-- Spanish Borrowing Costs Decline as Government Sells 6 Billion Euros Bills
-- Emma Ross-Thomas
-- 2010-07-20T08:43:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/spanish-borrowing-costs-decline-as-government-sells-6-billion-euros-bills.html

          
          
             Spain sold 12-month bills at an
average yield of 2.221 percent today, compared with 2.303
percent at the last sale on June 15.  
 It also sold 18-month bills at 2.331 percent, compared with
2.837 percent last month, the Bank of Spain said.  
          
          


  


        